# Commit Message Convention

All git commit messages MUST follow this format:

```
[type]: [DBOPS-<ticket>]: <description>
```

## Fields

- **type**: One of `fix`, `feat`, `techdebt`, `chore`
- **ticket**: The DBOPS Jira ticket number (e.g., `DBOPS-2054`)
- **description**: A concise summary of the change

## Examples

```
[fix]: [DBOPS-1960]: stores and certs errors as warning
[feat]: [DBOPS-2054]: add mysql-connector-j to download-common.sh
[techdebt]: [DBOPS-1980]: remove unused lpm binary from final images
[chore]: [DBOPS-2010]: bump Eclipse Temurin to 21.0.10_7
```

## Rules

- PR titles follow the same format
- If no Jira ticket exists, ask the user before committing
